        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Promotion Approval Workflows and Audit Trail"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Automated gates answer the question 'did the build pass?' The approval workflow answers 'should we ship it now?' \u2014 a judgement call that accounts for timing, business context, and risk tolerance. An audit trail records both answers permanently so any future incident, compliance review, or rollback can be attributed to a specific build and approver with full context."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "An approval that cannot be audited is not an approval \u2014 it is an undocumented gamble. Every production promotion must leave a record of who approved what, when, and on what evidence."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers how to implement the production approval gate using GitHub Environments, what information the approver sees before deciding, how to structure the audit trail, and how to query it for compliance and incident response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Promotion approval workflow: automated gates \u2192 manual approval \u2192 audit trail",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Environments as Approval Gates"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "GitHub Actions' Environments feature is the simplest way to implement a mandatory approval gate before a deployment job runs. When a job references an environment that has required reviewers configured, GitHub pauses the workflow and sends a notification to the named reviewers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting up the production environment"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Go to Repository Settings \u2192 Environments \u2192 New environment \u2192 name it 'production'"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Under 'Environment protection rules', enable 'Required reviewers' and add 1\u20132 named individuals or teams"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set 'Prevent self-review' so the engineer who wrote the PR cannot approve their own promotion"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set the wait timer to 8 hours \u2014 workflows waiting longer than that auto-cancel rather than blocking indefinitely"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/promote-to-prod.yml\njobs:\n  # ... gate validation jobs above ...\n\n  promote-production:\n    needs: [gate-3-full-validation]\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment:\n      name: production                        # triggers the approval gate\n      url: https://app.acme.com              # shown to reviewers in the UI\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Download manifest\n        uses: actions/download-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: deployment-manifest\n\n      - name: Print promotion summary for reviewer\n        run: |\n          python3 - <<'EOF'\n          import json\n          m = json.load(open(\"manifest.json\"))\n          print(\"=\" * 60)\n          print(\"PRODUCTION PROMOTION SUMMARY\")\n          print(\"=\" * 60)\n          print(f\"Build SHA:     {m['build_sha']}\")\n          print(f\"Image digest:  {m['image_digest'][:40]}...\")\n          print(f\"Prompt hash:   {m['prompt_hash']}\")\n          print(f\"Model:         {m['model']}\")\n          print(f\"Eval rate:     {m['eval_pass_rate']:.1%} (threshold 85%)\")\n          print(f\"Probes:        {m['security_probes_passed']}/{m['security_probes_total']} passed\")\n          print(f\"Gates passed:  {m['gates_passed']}\")\n          EOF\n\n      - name: Deploy canary\n        env:\n          KUBECONFIG: ${{ secrets.PROD_KUBECONFIG }}\n        run: |\n          IMAGE=$(jq -r .image_digest manifest.json)\n          kubectl set image deployment/claude-app-canary app=$IMAGE -n prod\n          kubectl rollout status deployment/claude-app-canary -n prod --timeout=300s\n\n      - name: Record approval in audit log\n        run: |\n          python3 scripts/audit_log.py append             --event \"production_approved\"             --build-sha \"$(jq -r .build_sha manifest.json)\"             --approver \"${{ github.actor }}\"             --run-id \"${{ github.run_id }}\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
